        <body>
            <div type="bibliography" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#Evangelidis1952"/>, <citedRange>302, no. 8, ph. 32</citedRange></bibl> (<bibl><ptr target="#BE"/> <citedRange>1956, 143.8</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/> <citedRange>15.388</citedRange></bibl>); <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneLhôte"/> <citedRange>36</citedRange></bibl> (<bibl><ptr target="#MéndezDosuna2008"/>, <citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl>); <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/> <citedRange>15A+16B</citedRange></bibl> (<bibl><ptr target="#CIOD"/> <citedRange>15A+16B+17B</citedRange></bibl> [last consulted 10/07/2026]).</p>
                <p>Cf.
                <bibl><ptr target="#Parker2016"/>, <citedRange>79 n.37</citedRange></bibl> (on <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐFάω</foreign>); <bibl><ptr target="#MéndezDosuna2024"/>, <citedRange>§4.1</citedRange></bibl> (on <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐFάω</foreign>).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc">
     <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="A">
     <ab>
      <lb n="1"/><persName><name nymRef="#Θέλυτος">Θέλυτος</name></persName> πότερά κα κατὰ χραν <space extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
<lb n="2"/>ἔχν τὰν γυναῖκα ἔχν κδοῖ <space extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
<lb n="3"/>hάπερ νῦν ἒ καὶ ἔϜν; <space extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
         </ab> 
                    </div>
<div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="B">
        <ab>
      <lb n="1"/><persName><name nymRef="#Θέλυτος">Θέλυτος</name></persName>
            </ab>
</div>
                </div>
            <div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
                <app loc="l. 2"><rdg><foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔχ ΝΚΟΔΟΙ</foreign></rdg> <note><ptr target="#IDodoneLhôte"/>, for which the author suggests the interpretation <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔχ ’ν Κδι</foreign></note> <rdg><foreign xml:lang="grc">ΗΟΔΟΙ</foreign></rdg> <note>Tsantsanoglou <foreign xml:lang="la">apud</foreign> <ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"></ptr></note> <rdg><foreign xml:lang="grc">ΕΧΟΝΚΟΔΟΙ</foreign> <ptr target="#CIOD"></ptr></rdg></app>
<app loc="l. 3"><rdg><foreign xml:lang="grc">ΚΑΠΕΡ</foreign></rdg> <note>Evangelidis, with an incorrect division of words in the first part of the line.</note></app>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
     <p>Thelytos whether he should depart, keeping the woman, keeping her in place, just as now, or leaving her. </p> 
                <p>Thelytos. </p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="es">
        <p>Télito si debe marchar conservando a la mujer, conservándola en el lugar, como ahora, o dejándola. </p> 
                <p>Télito. </p>
        </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Despite the clear reading of the inscription, its interpretation poses several difficulties, especially at the end of the second line, with the repetition of the participial form <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔχν</foreign> and the sequence <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΚΟΔΟΙ</foreign>, which Lhôte declines to interpret. Even so, the overall purport of the text is clear: the disjunctive πότερα and the participles indicate that the consultation concerns the alternative between keeping the woman and leaving her. The hypothesis proposed by Méndez Dosuna (<foreign xml:lang="grc">κδοῖ</foreign> = <foreign xml:lang="grc">καὶ ὁδοῖ</foreign>, cf. <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/></bibl> <foreign xml:lang="la">ad comm.</foreign>), tentatively adopted here, provides one possible explanation of the problematic sequence, although it is not without difficulties. </p>
                
                <p n="Ithaca results">In the geographical output, Epirus ranks first with a high probability according to Ithaca (93.87%), while the chronological distribution peaks at 450-440 BC (44.43%). See <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IDodoneOnline15A_2026_06_24.html">Ithaca results</ref> and <ref target="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IDodone/IDodoneOnline/refs/heads/main/ithaca-results/IDodoneOnline15A.md">metadata</ref>, and a snapshot of the <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IDodoneOnline15A_geographical-attribution_2026_06.jpg">geographical attribution</ref>.</p>
                </div>
        </body>
